Find vim user-manual at http://vimdoc.sourceforge.net/htmldoc/usr_toc.html
(Thanks Vim and all its contributors!!)

Mode: ~> Esc  // Normal Mode
Mode: ~> i    // Insert Mode
Mode:
More: ~> :set showmode

Exit: ~> ZZ     // Writes the file and exits
Exit: ~> :q!    // Discards the changes made to the file amd quits (! is for override)
More: ~> :e!    // Reloads original version of the file

Motion: ~> w    // moves to start of next word
Motion: ~> b    // moves to start of prev word
Motion: ~> e    // moves to end of current word
Motion: ~> ge   // moves to end of prev word